Overview

protocol for defining key manager methods

– getValueForServiceIds:preference:replacement:withCompletionHandler: required method

This Method is used to get the services,along with the keys associated with it

- (void)getValueForServiceIds:(NSArray<NSString*> *_Nonnull)serviceIds preference:(AIKMServiceDiscoveryPreference)preference replacement:(NSDictionary<NSString*,NSString*> *_Nullable)replacement withCompletionHandler:(void ( ^ _Nonnull ) ( NSDictionary<NSString*,AIKMService*> *_Nullable services , NSError *_Nullable error ))completionHandler

Parameters

serviceIds

one or more service ids in an array
preference

Country or language preference
replacement

replacement dictionary with map values for the URL query params
completionHandler

completionHandler returns a map with service Id mapped to service object

– getServiceExtensionWithServiceId:urlString:error: required method

Description : This Method is used to retrieve the bundled obfuscated keys.

- (NSDictionary<NSString*,NSString*> *_Nullable)getServiceExtensionWithServiceId:(NSString *_Nonnull)serviceId urlString:(NSString *_Nonnull)urlString error:(NSError *_Nullable *_Nullable)error

Parameters

serviceId

service id for the key set that is present in AIKMap.json
urlString

the url defined with key index in service discovery. The url should contain the index for key manager
error

error object

Return Value

dictionary with obfuscated keys. Returns nil if keys cannot be found
